laboratory_examinations.findings: Initial cultures demonstrated community-acquired methicillin-resistant S. aureus susceptible to clindamycin, gentamicin, rifampin, trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole, and vancomycin.
Cultures of the wound bed grew community-acquired methicillin-resistant S. aureus, susceptible to clindamycin, trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole, rifampin, and vancomycin.
Wound cultures grew community-acquired methicillin-resistant S. aureus that was susceptible to rifampin, trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole, clindamycin, and vancomycin.
